pr_review_comment_body:
I considered that... but then this:

```
    def builder(...):
        return "Jordan"

    @genty_deferred(builder)
    def test_method(self, name)
         ...
```
test_method would be called 6 times, with 1 letter each time :)

There's a lot of duplication here. Unfortunately the original code wasn't a great example to work from, so it's not your fault, but I think a better pattern would be to replace the existing code with a `$q.all` (https://docs.angularjs.org/api/ng/service/$q) and re-use the logic for getting new revision in both places. This would be a nice improvement over the old code as well.

E.g.:

```js
            $q.all([
                ThResultSetModel.getResultSetsFromRevision(
                    $scope.newProject.name, $scope.newRevision).then(function() {
                        $scope.newRevisionError = undefined;
                    },
                    function(error) {
                        $scope.newRevisionError = error;
                    }),
                ($scope.originalRevision) ? ThResultSetModel.getResultSetsFromRevision(
                    $scope.originalProject.name, $scope.originalRevision).then(function() {
                        $scope.originalRevisionError = undefined;
                    },
                    function(error) {
                        $scope.originalRevisionError = error;
                    })]).then(function() {
                        // we found result sets for both revisions, so have valid data
                        ...
                    });
```

Actually, looking at the history, it seems like I already asked you to do something like this in an earlier revision of the code. No matter, I know it's been a while since you've looked at this, but please implement this change before asking for another review.

@tiborsimko @lnielsen can I do something like:
```python
dictionary = {key: ' '.join(value) for key, value in six.iteritems(dictionary)}
```
instead?
